      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but it's more than just pitch, it's like a physical sensation in my chest, like a discordant harmonic. yesterday i was talking to my boss and he was saying everything was fine with my performance but the frequency he was hitting was so dissonant it actually made me feel nauseous. it felt like a literal clash of tones. do you think there's a specific way that resonance happens when someone is being deceptive?",
